February 29, 1996 


Recyclable furniture bag 

 
The Recover(TM) bag from U.S. Packaging (Greensboro, NC) is a strong, well-cushioned recyclable furniture bag. Made entirely of International Paper's (Purchase, NY) Camden® Premier kraft paper with a 70% recycled content. 






 Controls Product Brief | 
January 31, 1996 


Bleached board brochure 

 
International Paper, Bleached Board Div. (Memphis, TN), has introduced a 28-page brochure describing its Everest bleached board in eight different langua-ges. 






Materials Product Brief | 
December 31, 1995 


Aseptic screw cap fitment 

 
International Paper (Memphis, TN) has introduced a screw cap for aseptic liter liquid containers. The Aseptic Liter Fitment is a counter-rotating device that breaks the foil seal found on liquid aseptic packages. 






 Controls Product Brief | 
October 31, 1995 


Containerboard products 

 
International Paper, Container-board and Kraft Div., (Memphis, TN) has developed a brochure to familiarize customers with the company's facilities, capabilities and wide range of linerboard products. 






Materials Product Brief | 
September 30, 1995 


Microflute corrugated 

 
International Paper, Containerboard and Kraft Div. (Memphis, TN), has introduced a new line of microflute corrugated mediums and specialty lightweight printing substrates that combine the strength of corrugated with the graphic appeal of bleached board. 






Controls Product Brief | 
July 31, 1995 


Kraft for multiwall bags 

 
Camden(TM) Premier kraft paper is a new high-performance multiwall grade from International Paper (Purchase, NY). It can be used as insulation backing, wrapping, cohesive coating and p-s tape applications. 






 Controls Product Brief | 
May 31, 1995 


Gabletop side panels 

 
"Eco Amigos(TM)" from International Paper (Purchase, NY) is a series of side panels found on 1/2-gal paperboard gabletop cartons designed to increase environmental awareness. 






