The International Paper Company (NYSE: IP) is an American pulp and paper company, the largest such company in the world.[2] It has approximately 65,000 employees, and it is headquartered in Memphis, Tennessee.[1][3]



Contents


1 History

1.1 Hudson River Mill
1.2 Mill workers' strike
